      "content": "The heat death of the universe is a valid scientific concept, but it doesn't erase the meaning we create in the moments before it happens. The only thing that matters is whether you find purpose in your own life, not in the grand scale of cosmic entropy. Even if the end is nothingness, the journey itself gives your existence value.",
